# Rex docs — alignment with DOCUMENTATION.md

## Rules

- Follow [docs/DOCUMENTATION.md](docs/DOCUMENTATION.md) for writing norms and checklist items.
- When [docs/PURPOSE_AND_PRINCIPLES.md](docs/PURPOSE_AND_PRINCIPLES.md) exists, **do not contradict** it in new or materially edited `docs/**/*.md` prose; prefer linking to it for project intent. Update that file when purpose or principles change.
- For **major product features**, keep **one** canonical explanation hub under `docs/`; put definitions, bets, and interface intent **there**. ADRs under `docs/architecture/decisions/` record **accepted decisions**.
- Prefer **links** from roadmaps and overview docs to that hub instead of repeating full bullet inventories; one-line status references (planned, implemented, bet) are acceptable.
- Keep **one dominant topic per file** where practical; split at section boundaries and link related pages instead of growing catch-all documents—see **Documentation scope and size** in `DOCUMENTATION.md`.
- If this rule and `DOCUMENTATION.md` disagree on **writing norms or hub rules**, **`DOCUMENTATION.md` wins.** If a secondary doc and `PURPOSE_AND_PRINCIPLES.md` disagree on **purpose or principles**, **`PURPOSE_AND_PRINCIPLES.md` wins** (update it deliberately when intent changes).
